
1) back up drupal using public_html/drupalmod/backup_my_drupal

2) in public_html/swww run "~/drush/drush pm-update"

3) diff mydrupYYMMDD/htaccess public_html/swww/.htaccess
   if only my parts have changed, cp mydrupYYMMDD/htaccess public_html/swww/.htaccess

4) if ckeditor-mod is updated you have to reinstall ckeditor
     cd ~/public_html/swww/sites/all/modules/ckeditor
     unzip ~/public_html/drupalmod/copy_to_drupal/d7mods2014/ckeditor_4.4.3_standard.zip  -- get the full version of this (or greater) and use it instead of 4.2
     unzip ~/public_html/drupalmod/copy_to_drupal/d7mods2014/ckeditor_4.2_full.zip 

     Edit modules/ckeditor/ckeditor.config.js, which overrides the base modules/ckeditor/ckeditor/config.js, and add
         config.allowedContent=true;
     This turns off Advanced Content Filtering, so we can do what we want in the html
